# Deployment

When you make changes to this project, **always** provide the full deployment terminal commands the user can run, and use a **concrete commit message** that describes the change—never use placeholders like "Your commit message" or "Update".

Example:
```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "Fix board stretch: use fixed 32px grid so cells stay square"
git push
```
